	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002284_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 53 top left--><!--Hand 02 56119 top right--><!--Hand 03 <p>"M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Walker Brodie</p><p><unclear cert="high">2</unclear>9, Park Road,</p><p>Haverstock Hill,</p><p>London N. W."</p> top left-->
<lb/><p rend="right">8 Dover <choice><abbr>S<hi rend="sup underline">t</hi></abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice> Piccadilly</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">London</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">4 May 1865</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>Your note of 
<lb/>enquiry having gone 
<lb/>to my late address 
<lb/>I <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> it this 
<lb/>morning.</p>
<lb/><p>Last night I was 
<lb/>at D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton's 
<lb/>&amp; met the young man 
<lb/>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Brodie to whom 
<lb/>on a former occasion 
<lb/>I referred and he 
<lb/>told me that M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Silva 
<lb/>is now living at 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002284_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>Morley's Hotel, Charing 
<lb/>Cross. He says that 
<lb/>Silva is a Protestant 
<lb/>of Portuguese extraction 
<lb/>&amp; came thus far to 
<lb/>send his wife to 
<lb/>Boston U. S. He will 
<lb/>meet her next year 
<lb/>here. I dont know 
<lb/>that he is anything 
<lb/>of a Protestant more  
<lb/>than in name. The 
<lb/>Portuguese generally 
<lb/>are very much devoid 
<lb/>of religious convictions 
<lb/>but I think you  
<lb/>would get all the 
<lb/>information you 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002284_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>require from him.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Brodie is an 
<lb/>elder in D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton's 
<lb/>church though still 
<lb/>a young man and 
<lb/>would I feel sure 
<lb/>introduce you to Mr 
<lb/>Silva. I therefore 
<lb/>enclose  his card 
<lb/>rather than attempt 
<lb/>to give you second 
<lb/>rate information</p>
<lb/><p>As M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Brodie 
<lb/>is a Christian I 
<lb/>would suggest an 
<lb/>interview with 
<lb/>him first and 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002284_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/>you might depend on 
<lb/>his sympathy in 
<lb/>your objects. He 
<lb/>might give you 
<lb/>a clearer insight 
<lb/>into Silva's character 
<lb/>than I can.</p>
<lb/><p>Silva will know 
<lb/>the expenses better 
<lb/>than anyone else</p>
<lb/><p>Wishing you all 
<lb/>success I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Silva leaves for Loanda 
<lb/>by the end of this week</p>
			
